INSERT INTO `faq` VALUES (1,'What is the difference between a Virtual Private Server and a Dedicated Server?','\'Virtual\' means that it is not physical. Basically, it is like a shared hosting account but unlike a normal shared hosting account, each VPS has its own dedicated priority of the CPU, RAM and disk space so what you do will not affect the other VPS on the same hardware. You can reboot your VPS anytime you want and you will have root access so you can install what ever you want.\n<br><br>\nThink of it this way. A dedicated server is like owning and living in your own mansion. You can share or use it as completely yours. It is up to you.\n<br><Br>\nA virtual private server is like living in an apartment or a hotel room. You have your own doors, walls and private bathroom. You have the privacy of your own room and you can more or less  do anything you want. Of course, you will share the infrastructure with the other residents in the apartment building.',1,''),(14,'How many Servers can I buy?','You can buy as many as you like, at any level . \nYou can also expand your server to use up as much of our resources as you like!',0,'110713808c60b879159b7ef21c6fff0d167f'),(2,'Can I upgrade my server later without disrupting my users?','We have a mostly hot upgrade program, depending on which resource your are upgrading and how you need it upgraded. Adding more RAM requires a reboot. Expanding your root hard disk also requires a reboot. Although, if you would like to add an additional volume, we can do that without rebooting or disrupting your users.',0,'d9f1d6cc8b65d0c35baeb24daa76c2d82178'),(9,'What operating system do your servers run? ','Currently we only support Ubuntu and CentOS by default, but we are open to installing other operating systems if you require it. \n<br><br>\nWe will install any Intel-compatible operating system that you like for a flat install fee of $125. \n<br><br>\n<span style=\"red\">* If your operating system requires a license (I.E. Windows) you will be required to submit proof of a valid license before we can move forward. </span>',0,'42f5d946f6a0979c2f8f8e87529bb590fdfb'),(3,'What happens if I use all my allotted bandwidth?','No problem! Bandwidth limits are what we call \"Soft Limits\". In reality they are just billing tiers The base tier is 100 GB of transfer. \n<br><br>\nIf you go over, you simply roll into the next tier. This way you only get charged for what you use.\n',0,'4554dd54304b7c0ac17daeb6d0999bd7dfeb'),(4,'Can I run windows? ','Currently we only support the last two versions of Ubuntu and CentOS by default. But we are open to running Windows Server in one of our virtual servers if you require it. \n<br><br>\nWe will install Windows for a flat fee of $125. \n<br><br>\n<span style=\"color: red;\">\n* You will be required to submit proof of a valid Windows Server license before we can start.<br>\n* We do not offer technical support for Windows Server. You run it at your own risk.<br>\n* Our standard disk size adjustment methods will not work in Windows Server. So if you want to increase your disk space later. you will have to pay a one time service fee to do so. (Ask Support for pricing)\n</span>',0,'b154e3425acfc4e7297d275c5a3bf4b87045'),(5,'What is the air speed vilocity of an air laden swallow?','African Or European?',0,'0c86143361551320774cf5e72ef889d67913'),(13,'Do you really want to Destroy All Humans?','VPS Robot is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Destroy All Humans LLC.\n<br><br>\nNo, we do not want to destroy you. \n<br><br>\nWe\'re a company of nerds who love robots and robot-related fiction.\n<br><br>\nWe are also obsessed with the art of automation and replacing human work loads with computer code. \n<br><br>\nIt\'s why we can offer such competitive pricing. We have automated the tasks of several maintenance crews. Passing the savings on to you!<br>',0,'cce7614f8f09f8a7c6ec865439959700bdf9');
